    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1256"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1256">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.2311/34.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Governor of Texas</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin, Texas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 10, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram [of February 9] received. Am advised that railroad communication
                    between Juárez and Chihuahua is open, but south of Chihuahua the railroad is in
                    hands of revolting party.</p>
                <p>If Mexican troops pass through Texas from Eagle Pass to Juárez, is there any
                    assurance that they will not be met with armed resistance in attempting to enter
                    Juárez from Texas?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">O. B. Colquitt.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
